Join the Nation's Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Dak Prescott accepts offensive ROY award with Ezekiel Elliott Alysha Tsuji , USA TODAY 8:16 a.m. ET Feb. 5, 2017 
(Photo: Invision for NFL) 
Dak Prescott was named NFL offensive rookie of the year on Saturday. When he went up on stage, he brought teammate Ezekiel Elliott with him, the one he beat out for the award. And the first thing Prescott said was, "Do we have a knife so I can cut this in half?" Dak Prescott wanted to share his Offensive Rookie of the Year trophy with his buddy Zeke. pic.twitter.com/pr5UHkVcQy
